==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Niobe
<hw>Ni"o*be</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>Nioba</ets>,
<ets>Niobe</ets>, Gr. <?/.]</ety> <fld>(Class. Myth.)</fld> <def>The
daughter of <persfn>Tantalus</persfn>, and wife of
<persfn>Amphion</persfn>, king of <city>Thebes</city>. Her pride in her
children provoked <persfn>Apollo</persfn> and <persfn>Diana</persfn>,
who slew them all. Niobe herself was changed by the gods into
stone.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

